🧮 Mini Boss-Level Calculator 😎
Welcome to your very own Mini Calculator that can add, subtract, multiply, and divide two numbers — like a total boss! 💪✨
Built with Python and a dash of flair, this script is perfect for beginners who want to learn the basics of handling numbers and user input.

🚀 What It Does
This calculator script:

Asks the user to input two numbers

Performs:

➕ Addition

➖ Subtraction

✖️ Multiplication

➗ Division

Prints out the results with some fun and emoji-packed commentary! 🎉

📝 How to Use
Make sure you have Python 3 installed.

Save the script in a file, for example: calculator.py

Run the script:

bash
Copy code
python calculator.py
When prompted, enter two numbers (decimals welcome!).

Sit back and enjoy your results. 😎

💡 Example
text
Copy code
Enter the first number: 10
Enter the second number: 3

Results of your two numbers:
Sum: 13.0
Difference: 7.0
Product: 30.0
Quotient: 3.3333333333333335
⚠️ Note on Division
This script assumes the user will not divide by zero. If you're feeling wild, you can add a try/except block to catch that later! 😅

✨ Features
Accepts decimal numbers via float()

Outputs each result clearly with labels and emojis

Educational and beginner-friendly comments throughout the code

📁 File Contents
calculator.py – the Python script with detailed comments and fun emoji guides

📚 Learn More
Want to go further?

Try adding error handling

Let the user choose the operation

Wrap it in a loop to do multiple calculations
